external_knowledge:
- 'scarcity signals' refers to the reorder level of products;
- 'common whisper' represents the average reorder level for the 'Electronics' category;
- 'lesser-known corners' implies warehouses with a product having fewer than 10 instances in inventory;
- 'electronic treasures' means products in the 'Electronics' category.

"Admin users" refer to users with the 'admin' role;
"a few items" refers to a quantity greater than 1;
"a significant amount" refers to a cost greater than 150.
